<ul id="mwC2g"><li id="mwC2k"><i id="mwC2o">Panel IV: Contemporary Implications</i></li></ul>
<dl id="mwC2s"><dd id="mwC2w"><ul id="mwC20"><li id="mwC24"><cite id="CITEREFCarter2012" class="citation journal cs1">Carter, William M. Jr. (November 2012). "The Thirteenth Amendment and pro-equality speech". <i>Columbia Law Review</i>. <b>112</b> (7). Columbia Law School: <span class="nowrap">1855â</span>1881. JSTOR<span typeof="mw:Entity">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/41708166" class="external text external">41708166</a>. SSRN<span typeof="mw:Entity">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2166859" class="external text external">2166859</a>.</cite> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20151117021729/http://columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Carter-W.M..pdf" class="external text external" id="mwC3E">Pdf.</a></li>
